# mem-constant (project-local)

This project was scaffolded with **`mem-constant init`**. Canonical specs live under **`docs/mem-constant/`** (copied from the installed package version).

## Session carryover (read first in a new chat)

Before your **first substantive reply** in a **new** chat, **read** **`.mem-constant/last-session.md`** at the project root (next to **`mem-constant.yaml`**) if that file **exists** and is **non-empty**. Treat it as continuity from the prior session: goals, decisions, and pending work. **Do not skip it** because the user did not repeat it in their latest message.

If the user asks for a **`handoff`** for the next session, follow **`docs/mem-constant/global-handoff-template.md`**, then remind them they can save it with **`mem-constant carryover write`** (stdin or a file path).

## Authority

- **MemPalace** (or your chosen archive): durable facts and decisions.
- **Working cache** (e.g. Claude Mem): short-horizon thread continuity.

## Sync

Reconcile at **new chat**, **new agent**, and **end of milestone**: promote what stays true into the archive; trim the cache.

## Handoff

When context rolls over, use the **global handoff** format in `docs/mem-constant/global-handoff-template.md` (user says `handoff` or equivalent).
